value.value: A protein that is a translation product of the human GLA gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

A protein that is a translation product of the human GLB1 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof in eukaryotes. The eukaryotic-type beta-galactosidase contains a Glycosyl hydrolases family 35 (Pfam:PF01301) domain instead of the Glycosyl hydrolases family 2 (Pfam:PF00703) domain typical of the bacterial-type.
